    <div class="content">
      <p>Modern fertility treatments have evolved significantly over the last decade. With the integration of AI-driven embryo selection and personalized hormonal protocols, success rates are at an all-time high, offering hope to thousands of aspiring parents worldwide.</p>
      
      <h2 id="section1">Understanding Biological Markers</h2>
      <p>The first step in any modern IVF journey is a deep dive into biological markers. We no longer look at just age; we look at the cellular environment. Factors like AMH levels, ovarian reserve, and genetic mapping provide a blueprint that allows us to customize the medication dosage for each specific patient.</p>
      <p>By analyzing these markers, we can predict how a patient will respond to stimulation, minimizing the risk of Ovarian Hyperstimulation Syndrome (OHSS) while maximizing the number of healthy eggs retrieved.</p>

      <h2 id="section2">Cryopreservation Breakthroughs</h2>
      <p>Vitrification technology has revolutionized how we store eggs and embryos, maintaining nearly 99% viability across years of storage. This "flash-freezing" technique prevents the formation of ice crystals that previously damaged delicate cells.</p>
      <p>This has empowered women to take control of their reproductive timelines, allowing for social egg freezing and providing a safety net for those undergoing medical treatments like chemotherapy.</p>

      <div class="content-cta">
