      <h2 id="section3">AI in Embryo Selection</h2>
      <p>One of the most exciting developments in 2026 is the use of Artificial Intelligence in the embryology lab. AI algorithms can now analyze time-lapse images of developing embryos to identify the ones with the highest implantation potential.</p>
      <p>This non-invasive selection process complements traditional PGT-A (Preimplantation Genetic Testing), ensuring that the most viable embryo is chosen for transfer, significantly reducing the "time to pregnancy."</p>

      <h2 id="section4">The Role of Lifestyle and Nutrition</h2>
      <p>While technology is vital, the "holistic IVF" approach emphasizes the internal environment of the body. We now integrate nutritional counseling, stress management, and acupuncture into our protocols.</p>
      <p>Studies have shown that reducing oxidative stress through diet and specific antioxidants can improve egg and sperm quality, creating a more receptive uterine lining for the embryo.</p>
